The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, April 27: Infrastructure growth dipped 0.9 per cent in 2005-06, which reduced the overall growth rate to 4.9 per cent from 5.8 per cent in the previous year. The decline was largely due to a negative growth in crude oil and slump in petroleum products and finished steel. Cement was the only performing sector, which doubled its growth to 12.3 per cent during the period compared with 6.6 in the previous year. The six industries, including crude petroleum, petroleum refinery products, coal, electricity, cement and finished steel have a combined weight of 26.7 per cent in the index of industrial production with base 1993-94.

 Mumbai, April 27: The board of Zee Telefilms today approved hiving off of the direct consumer services business into a new entity ? ASC Enterprises.

 New Delhi, April 27: The cabinet today approved the Bangalore Metro Rail project involving a cost of Rs 5,453 crore. The project will cover a distance of 33 km and be completed in five years.

 New Delhi, April 27: The department of telecom is planning a cabinet note suggesting that telecom firms with no foreign direct investment should be allowed to have foreign chief executives.

 Mumbai, April 27: United Breweries today said it would split its equity shares in the 1:10 ratio.




